added.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
added.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

added.title: Fiesta Day
added.description: The Bears party it up with a living piñatas for Fiesta Day. Wanting the festivities to never end, Grizz wishes for it to be Fiesta Day everyday.

added.title: Baba Yaga House
added.description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

added.title: Bears in the Dark
added.description: The Bears search for their missing box in a dark and scary cave.

added.title: Apoca-lice Now
added.description: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

added.title: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
added.description: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

added.title: Look Who's Clocking
added.description: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

added.title: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
added.description: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: Red, White and Bruised/Beaky Buzzard Gags: Bunny/Jet Porkpelled
added.description: Tweety Bird builds a nest in a military base to keep safe from Sylvester. Beaky Buzzard goes hunting. Porky tries Daffy Duck's new jet pack.

added.title: Emotional Support Duck/End of the Leash Gags: Tennis/Adopt Me
added.description: Porky pretends Daffy is his emotional support duck. Foghorn plays a painful game of tennis. Charlie Dog lets everyone know he's the greatest dog ever.

added.title: Rage Rover/To Hive and to Hold/Battle Stations
added.description: Marvin the Martian proves no match for NASA's Mars Rover. Taz learns about bees… the hard way. Porky and Daffy can't agree on a radio station.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he's too short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: The Upply Strike Back!
added.description: Cole and the Upply arrive at the Skull Sorcerer's keep in the hopes of rescuing Lloyd and the other ninja. But in order to do so, Cole will need to retrieve his mother's fabled swords, the Blades of Deliverance, which are hidden somewhere inside the keep!

added.title: The Son of Lilly
added.description: The battle for the fate of Shintaro Mountain concludes!

added.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
added.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

added.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
added.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League/The Ancient Elder
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!/The Ancient Elder: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

added.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
added.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

added.title: Mi Guardaespaldas
added.description: Cuando Zombozo hipnotiza a toda la clase de panadería del abuelo Max, Ben y Gwen son los encargados de limpiar el desastre. Pero las cosas se complican aún más cuando Zombozo presenta a su nuevo guardaespaldas: iKevin 11!

added.title: Neumaticos de la Fortuna
added.description: Las compras en la tienda de segunda mano del equipo Tennyson se ven interrumpidas por el último atraco a alta velocidad de LaGrange -que ahora cuenta con la ayuda de un auto de carreras electromagnético superrápido- y Ben debe convencer a Kevin 11 para que ayude a detener la ola de robos del trotamundos endemoniado con la velocidad.

added.title: El Calor del Momento
added.description: Cuando Ben se deshace sin dificultad de los Climáticos, el equipo de Tennyson viaja a un centro de esquí para divertirse en la nieve. Pero cuando Ben se topa con los Climáticos una vez más, esta vez tendrá que vérselas con su fuerza iahora que Kevin 11 usó sus poderes de Bootleg para desbloquear sus controles emocionales!

added.title: Diagrama de Vin
added.description: Cuando Ben ve que Vin Etanol se asombra con los conocimientos automovilísticos de Kevin, los celos de Ben lo convencen de que tiene que superar a Kevin antes de que el joven convenza a Vin de adoptar su lado malo en una carrera a beneficio.

added.title: Una Situacion Pegajosa
added.description: Lo único que Ben quiere hacer es evitar que la Abeja Reina robe un banco, pero cuando Kevin aparece para intentar ser el héroe y quedarse con toda la gloria, Ben tiene que salvar a todos por segunda vez en el día o terminar embadurnado en miel.

added.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
added.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

added.title: Isla Dyer
added.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

added.title: El Ascenso
added.description: Cole, los de abajo, la princesa Vania y Wu salen de la montaña para enfrentarse al malvado Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Los de Arriba Contra Atacan
added.description: Cole y los de abajo llegan para rescatar a los Ninjas. Para ello, Cole tendrá que recuperar las espadas legendarias, las Espadas de la Liberación.

added.title: El Hijo de Lilly
added.description: iLa batalla por el destino de la Montaña Shintaro concluye!

added.title: Apoca-piojos ahora
added.description: Cuando Chef pacta una tregua con los piojos seleccionando tres niños que los "alberguen" en sus cabezas, Courtney instiga una guerra de niños contra piojos.

added.title: Gno mas buen senor
added.description: Cuando  la guardería es invadida por gnomos malvados, Duncan se encuentra en el equipo equivocado.

added.title: Fuera de hora
added.description: Cuando las advertencias de Harold de no meterse con el reloj son ignoradas, los niños están obligados a salvarse a sí mismos cuando Duncan abre un agujero en la trama del tiempo.

added.title: Harold Matamoscas y el caliz de moscas
added.description: Después de descubrir lo que cree que es una varita mágica, Owen convierte accidentalmente a Harold en una mosca común.

added.title: Venganza apestosa
added.description: Cuando una mofeta viene a buscar su venganza anual contra el Chef, Duncan ve una oportunidad de tomarse unas vacaciones de la guardería.

added.title: Grass is Greener
added.description: MOE wants to know what it's like to be a member of the Batwheels, but the bot gets more than he bargained for when Bam invites him along for an exciting mission to stop Poison Ivy.

added.title: Holidays on Ice
added.description: Frustrated by the Batwheels' holiday distractions, Batwing decides to "go solo" to thwart Mr. Freeze's evil Christmas-time plot. But Batwing soon realizes how hard it is to stop Mr. Freeze on her own!

added.title: Blast Off
added.description: When Marvin the Martian crash lands in Looneyburg, he's in a hurry to leave and hires The Looney Builders to build him a spaceship.

added.title: K-9: Space Puppy
added.description: Marvin the Martian hires The Looney Builders to build a doghouse on Mars for his puppy, K-9. Daffy soon bonds with K-9 and comes up with a plan to prolong their playtime.

added.title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
added.description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

added.title: Yip Yip Tree Tree/The Snowman Scarecrow
added.description: When the ornaments on the Pretty Big City tree break, the Mechas must build new ones and save the holidays for their friends./It's time for Zee and MacBarm's gift exchange, but the snowman scarecrow Zee made for MacBarm keeps blowing away!

added.title: Something to Remember
added.description: On the last day of Yong Bao's visit to Sodor, his friends dig up a giant keepsake to help him remember them.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Sandy Versus the Storm
added.description: When a big storm approaches, Thomas and company must complete all a week's worth of deliveries by the end-of-the-workday whistle, but when Sandy needs repairs, Thomas and the gang will realize just how important Sandy is to the team!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: An UnbeLEAFable Day
added.description: While the trains are setting up for the Vicarstown Fall Festival, Thomas is feeling down about the end of summer and the changing weather.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Ghost Train
added.description: Percy has to deliver the mail on Halloween when everyone knows the legendary Ghost Train comes out! Thomas rolls along to help Percy face his fears, but when a "real" Ghost Train appears... things get almost spooky.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Soggy Cereal
added.description: Blippi wonders why does cereal get soggy?

added.title: Sneeze
added.description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

added.title: Snowflake
added.description: It's an icy day, and a very cold Blippi heads to the sky to find out how snowflakes are made. Way up high in the winter clouds he helps Mimi, an athletic dust particle, achieve her goal to build up enough ice crystals and transform into a unique and awesome snowflake. Way to be original Mimi!

added.title: Recycle Stomp
added.description: Mei, the children and some animals are in the park collecting trash to recycle!

added.title: The Silly Little song
added.description: The other children and the animals all get together to cheer Rishi up with a funny, silly song.

added.title: The Penguin Dance
added.description: Rico the penguin is visiting Lellobee city farm… and he's travelled all the way from the North pole!

added.title: Pouting Match
added.description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

added.title: Wise Quacker
added.description: Melissa gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but she takes the jokes too far.

added.title: Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
added.description: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

added.title: Loose Change
added.description: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change.

added.title: Act Your Age
added.description: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.
